### Security Requirements
**CRITICAL: Always follow these security practices:**

1. **Input Sanitization**: Always sanitize user input using WordPress built-in functions
   ```php
   $id = intval( $request->get_param( 'id' ) );
   $title = sanitize_text_field( $request->get_param( 'title' ) );
   $content = sanitize_textarea_field( $request->get_param( 'content' ) );
   $email = sanitize_email( $request->get_param( 'email' ) );
   $url = esc_url_raw( $request->get_param( 'url' ) );
   $html = wp_kses_post( $request->get_param( 'html_content' ) );
   $array = array_map( 'absint', $request->get_param( 'ids' ) );
   ```

2. **Output Escaping**: Always escape output
   ```php
   esc_html( $text );           // For plain text
   esc_attr( $attribute );      // For HTML attributes
   esc_url( $url );             // For URLs
   esc_js( $string );           // For inline JavaScript
   wp_kses_post( $html );       // For post content with allowed HTML
   wp_kses( $html, $allowed );  // For custom allowed HTML
   ```

3. **Database Queries**: Use prepared statements with $wpdb
   ```php
   global $wpdb;
   
   // SELECT with prepare
   $results = $wpdb->get_results(
       $wpdb->prepare(
           "SELECT * FROM {$wpdb->prefix}pm_projects WHERE id = %d AND status = %s",
           $id,
           $status
       )
   );
   
   // INSERT with prepare
   $wpdb->insert(
       $wpdb->prefix . 'pm_projects',
       [
           'title'      => $title,
           'status'     => $status,
           'created_by' => get_current_user_id(),
       ],
       [ '%s', '%s', '%d' ]
   );
   
   // UPDATE with prepare
   $wpdb->update(
       $wpdb->prefix . 'pm_projects',
       [ 'title' => $title ],
       [ 'id' => $id ],
       [ '%s' ],
       [ '%d' ]
   );
   ```

4. **Nonce Verification**: Verify nonces for form submissions and AJAX
   ```php
   // Creating nonce
   wp_nonce_field( 'pm_save_project', 'pm_nonce' );
   
   // Verifying nonce
   if ( ! wp_verify_nonce( $_POST['pm_nonce'], 'pm_save_project' ) ) {
       wp_die( __( 'Security check failed.', 'wedevs-project-manager' ) );
   }
   
   // For REST API - nonce is handled automatically when using cookie authentication
   ```

5. **Capability Checks**: Always verify user permissions
   ```php
   // Check WordPress capabilities
   if ( ! current_user_can( 'manage_options' ) ) {
       return new \WP_Error( 'forbidden', __( 'Permission denied.', 'wedevs-project-manager' ) );
   }
   
   // Check plugin-specific capabilities
   if ( ! pm_user_can( 'edit_project', $project_id ) ) {
       return new \WP_Error( 'forbidden', __( 'You cannot edit this project.', 'wedevs-project-manager' ) );
   }
   ```

